WEBVTT

00:00.015 --> 00:02.164
(Stahma) Previously on <i>Defiance...</i>

00:02.199 --> 00:05.200
This is our best chance
to take Rahm by surprise.

00:05.234 --> 00:06.601
I don't want him in there.

00:06.636 --> 00:09.104
It's not your choice. I'm going.

00:09.138 --> 00:12.908
[somber music]

00:12.942 --> 00:14.976
- Just be careful.
- Always.

00:15.011 --> 00:18.580
[all grunting]

00:18.614 --> 00:20.315
No!

00:20.349 --> 00:21.349
[explosion booms]

00:21.384 --> 00:23.618
No!

00:23.653 --> 00:27.355
(Irisa) You gambled. If it
had worked, you'd be a hero.

00:27.390 --> 00:28.657
(Nolan) Yeah, but it didn't.

00:28.691 --> 00:30.558
They trusted me, they followed me,

00:30.593 --> 00:32.259
and now they're dead because of me.

00:32.295 --> 00:34.429
Rahm Tak is setting up camp
right outside the stasis nets.

00:34.463 --> 00:37.265
I've got an idea. It's a suicide mission.

00:37.300 --> 00:41.069
I'm offering you a chance at redemption.

00:41.103 --> 00:45.106
- Posthumously.
- Ah... there's the catch.

00:45.141 --> 00:48.410
[warbling tone]

00:48.444 --> 00:49.911
What are you still doing here? Go.

00:49.946 --> 00:51.413
My body is yours.

00:51.447 --> 00:53.048
[dramatic music]

00:53.082 --> 00:54.549
Agh!

00:54.583 --> 00:55.550
[all yelling]

00:55.584 --> 00:57.852
[explosion booms]

00:57.887 --> 01:00.021
[rumbling]

01:00.056 --> 01:01.990
♪ ♪

01:05.728 --> 01:08.663
[foreboding music]

01:08.698 --> 01:11.666
[low growling]

01:11.701 --> 01:14.669
[panting]

01:14.704 --> 01:16.571
♪ ♪

01:16.605 --> 01:18.206
[gasps]

01:18.240 --> 01:20.375
♪ ♪

01:20.409 --> 01:22.577
[banging]

01:22.611 --> 01:25.146
♪ ♪

01:25.181 --> 01:28.116
[heavy breathing]

01:28.150 --> 01:31.252
[growling]

01:31.287 --> 01:34.522
[ominous music]

01:34.557 --> 01:35.757
[growling]

01:35.791 --> 01:38.793
♪ ♪

01:38.828 --> 01:41.997
[growling]

01:42.031 --> 01:46.601
♪ ♪

01:46.635 --> 01:47.602
[impact]

01:47.636 --> 01:50.605
[screaming]

01:50.639 --> 01:53.108
[growling]

01:53.142 --> 01:55.643
[tearing]

01:55.678 --> 01:57.045
[cries]

01:57.079 --> 01:58.146
[roaring]

01:58.180 --> 02:00.648
[screams]

02:00.683 --> 02:02.417
[tearing]

02:02.451 --> 02:06.154
(Amanda) The town of
Defiance has been attacked

02:06.188 --> 02:09.056
by something monstrous.

02:09.091 --> 02:11.860
Hate.

02:11.894 --> 02:13.928
Hate drove the Votanis Collective

02:13.963 --> 02:15.697
to collapse that tunnel,

02:15.731 --> 02:19.601
brutally murdering 27 brave heroes.

02:19.635 --> 02:23.972
Their faces are up here,
memorialized on this wall.

02:24.006 --> 02:29.778
It's a testament to our spirit
that hate took us by surprise.

02:29.812 --> 02:32.213
And for our ignorance,

02:32.248 --> 02:35.850
we paid a very high price...

02:35.885 --> 02:37.352
in blood.

02:37.386 --> 02:40.688
The blood of husbands and wives,

02:40.723 --> 02:44.025
sons...

02:44.060 --> 02:46.194
and daughters.

02:46.228 --> 02:49.330
We owe them a debt we can never repay.

02:49.365 --> 02:51.599
Rahm Tak and his militia are dead

02:51.634 --> 02:54.469
thanks to the sacrifice made by Datak Tarr

02:54.503 --> 02:56.071
and the 27 brave soldiers

02:56.105 --> 03:00.041
who died bringing the
fight to Rahm's doorstep.

03:00.076 --> 03:02.110
I promise you

03:02.144 --> 03:04.379
these lights were not extinguished in vain.

03:04.413 --> 03:07.382
[somber music]

03:07.416 --> 03:09.517
♪ ♪

03:09.552 --> 03:12.153
The lawkeeper would
like to say a few words.

03:12.188 --> 03:13.521
No!

03:17.560 --> 03:22.230
I will not listen to the
man who killed my son.

03:22.264 --> 03:24.365
- You butcher!
- [crowd gasps and murmurs]

03:24.400 --> 03:30.105
♪ ♪

03:30.139 --> 03:31.172
[door slams]

03:31.207 --> 03:39.214
♪ ♪

03:47.857 --> 03:51.426
Things go wrong in war.

03:57.600 --> 03:59.167
[exhales]

04:01.270 --> 04:05.874
I made a mistake. People died.

04:08.577 --> 04:10.645
I'm sorry.

04:10.679 --> 04:15.984
♪ ♪

04:16.017 --> 04:19.220
I wish I could change that.

04:19.255 --> 04:20.522
But I can't.

04:23.125 --> 04:25.894
I... I... I don't have
anything else to say.

04:25.928 --> 04:28.129
It's okay.

04:28.164 --> 04:30.431
[sighs]

04:30.466 --> 04:38.773
♪ ♪

04:41.177 --> 04:44.512
Alak. My condolences.

04:44.547 --> 04:47.148
Keep 'em.

04:47.183 --> 04:50.118
My mother... you know
where she is, don't you?

04:50.152 --> 04:51.419
I do not.

04:51.453 --> 04:55.390
But wherever she is, one
may assume her heart grieves.

04:55.424 --> 04:56.457
[murmurs]

04:56.492 --> 04:58.760
Well, she's a coward and a murderer.

04:58.794 --> 05:01.262
You do not understand
the position she was in.

05:01.297 --> 05:05.200
You're right. I don't.

05:05.234 --> 05:08.169
If you do happen to see my
mother, you could tell her

05:08.204 --> 05:10.805
that the mayor may have
pardoned her, but I haven't.

05:10.839 --> 05:13.908
She comes anywhere near me
or my son, I'll kill her.

05:18.314 --> 05:21.316
[speaking native language]

05:23.118 --> 05:26.955
I brought you some food from the market.

05:26.989 --> 05:29.457
I'm afraid I don't have
much of an appetite.

05:29.491 --> 05:30.558
[bottles clink]

05:30.593 --> 05:32.994
Hmm.

05:33.028 --> 05:36.030
Were you able to make contact with Alak?

05:36.065 --> 05:38.166
He did not have kind words for you.

05:39.702 --> 05:43.304
As expected.

05:43.339 --> 05:44.572
Was he well?

05:44.607 --> 05:48.676
Well enough to attend the
funeral of your husband.

05:48.711 --> 05:52.614
There was a funeral?

05:52.648 --> 05:54.449
Did Alak organize it?

05:54.483 --> 05:56.384
No, the mayor.

05:56.418 --> 05:58.753
I took the liberty of attending

05:58.787 --> 06:03.091
assuming that you'd be anxious for details.

06:03.125 --> 06:07.996
Why would Amanda
Rosewater honor my husband?

06:08.030 --> 06:10.431
He was hung as a traitor.

06:10.466 --> 06:13.101
Yet he was honored alongside those

06:13.135 --> 06:16.371
who fell fighting Rahm Tak.

06:16.405 --> 06:20.041
Datak walked that bomb
into the Votanis camp.

06:20.075 --> 06:23.211
He martyred himself to save the town.

06:26.315 --> 06:29.517
Dying in the service
of others is not the end

06:29.551 --> 06:31.753
I would have expected for my husband.

06:31.787 --> 06:34.489
It is possible he did it for you.

06:34.523 --> 06:37.558
[somber music]

06:37.593 --> 06:38.893
How so?

06:38.927 --> 06:40.295
Datak secured a pardon

06:40.329 --> 06:43.331
as a condition of his sacrifice.

06:43.365 --> 06:45.566
[sobbing]

06:45.601 --> 06:50.338
You are free to return home.

06:50.372 --> 06:52.340
Hmm.

06:52.374 --> 06:58.813
♪ ♪

06:58.847 --> 07:00.982
[door rattles and creaks]

07:01.016 --> 07:04.519
[footsteps tapping]

07:04.553 --> 07:07.288
You okay?

07:07.323 --> 07:11.359
That was Indur who
walked out, Zero's father.

07:12.895 --> 07:15.797
And that's what's left of Zero's rifle?

07:18.967 --> 07:20.601
What are you gonna do?

07:20.636 --> 07:23.137
Figure his old man should have it.

07:23.172 --> 07:24.639
I'll bring it to him.

07:24.673 --> 07:26.974
No, this one's on me.

07:27.009 --> 07:29.777
You can't think that's a good idea.

07:29.812 --> 07:33.948
- I don't.
- Then why are you going?

07:33.982 --> 07:37.185
'Cause if this was yours,

07:37.219 --> 07:39.087
if that had been you burned to ash

07:39.121 --> 07:42.223
down in that tunnel and not Indur's boy...

07:50.265 --> 07:53.301
It's what needs to be done.

07:53.335 --> 07:55.970
[door rattles and creaks]

07:56.004 --> 07:57.438
[door thuds]

07:57.473 --> 08:00.441
[dramatic music]

08:00.476 --> 08:03.594
♪ ♪

08:03.629 --> 08:08.629
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

08:10.000 --> 08:16.074
Learn the unknown English words
of this movie at www.skeebdo.com

08:29.171 --> 08:31.038
Indur?

08:33.275 --> 08:37.211
Thought you should have this.

08:37.246 --> 08:40.881
My son used to make stew every Tuesday.

08:42.683 --> 08:45.019
Do you know what day today is?

08:47.589 --> 08:49.557
I don't want a broken rifle.

08:49.591 --> 08:52.326
I want my son.

08:52.361 --> 08:55.630
I want him sitting across
from me at that table

08:55.664 --> 08:58.099
complaining about how his
stew is never spicy enough.

08:58.133 --> 09:01.869
Can you give me that?

09:01.904 --> 09:03.504
No, sir, I cannot.

09:03.539 --> 09:05.039
[gun clicks]

09:05.073 --> 09:08.142
[breathing heavily]

09:08.177 --> 09:11.579
[somber music]

09:11.613 --> 09:14.682
So how's this gonna end?

09:14.716 --> 09:17.552
♪ ♪

09:17.586 --> 09:20.521
[grunts and gasps]

09:20.556 --> 09:27.462
♪ ♪

09:33.769 --> 09:36.704
Hey, this way. Where's Nolan?

09:36.738 --> 09:38.840
- Busy.
- Is he okay?

09:38.874 --> 09:41.375
He'll be fine. What have you got?

09:41.410 --> 09:43.744
Sanitation found the body this morning.

09:43.779 --> 09:45.246
[echoing screams]

09:45.280 --> 09:48.015
Indogene victim.

09:48.050 --> 09:49.851
[foreboding music]

09:49.885 --> 09:51.352
The stasis nets are down.

09:51.386 --> 09:54.455
Maybe a sabre wolf wandered
in through Bissel Pass.

09:54.490 --> 09:58.659
A sabre wolf wouldn't break from the pack.

09:58.694 --> 10:00.661
This was something else.

10:03.465 --> 10:05.066
[Amanda grunts]

10:05.100 --> 10:07.768
Doc?

10:07.803 --> 10:11.138
Doc! We got a body here.

10:11.173 --> 10:13.341
Ugh.

10:13.375 --> 10:16.143
Doc!

10:16.178 --> 10:17.979
That's weird. She's usually open by now.

10:18.013 --> 10:20.114
(Doc) Been memorizing my office hours?

10:20.148 --> 10:25.086
Obviously you know me
better than I know myself.

10:25.120 --> 10:27.722
Who's the stiff?

10:29.525 --> 10:32.693
(Indur) Did my son ever
tell you about Lucy?

10:32.728 --> 10:36.097
Lucy?

10:36.131 --> 10:38.165
I'm afraid I didn't have the privilege.

10:38.200 --> 10:41.168
I built it for him.

10:41.203 --> 10:45.740
He named it after a human
girl who lived down the way.

10:45.774 --> 10:47.708
He was fond of her, but
she was young and fickle

10:47.743 --> 10:49.810
and broke his heart.

10:49.845 --> 10:52.380
Zero used to say that this weapon

10:52.414 --> 10:55.950
was the second most beautiful
thing he'd ever seen.

11:01.089 --> 11:03.324
So he named it after the first.

11:10.232 --> 11:15.002
Indur, we all lose people we care about.

11:15.037 --> 11:16.637
What's important in all of this

11:16.672 --> 11:19.340
is that you don't lose yourself,

11:19.374 --> 11:22.176
not to the anger, not
to the ache in your gut,

11:22.210 --> 11:23.878
not to the anything.

11:27.482 --> 11:30.451
I have nothing left to lose.

11:31.920 --> 11:34.322
And that's all because of you.

11:34.356 --> 11:37.124
[somber music]

11:37.159 --> 11:40.761
You're right.

11:40.796 --> 11:45.333
I'm just a grunt. I'm not a general.

11:45.367 --> 11:46.867
I led 'em all down into that hole,

11:46.902 --> 11:49.604
and I got 'em all killed,

11:49.638 --> 11:53.007
your son included.

11:53.041 --> 11:56.377
And I'm gonna have to live with
that for the rest of my life,

11:56.411 --> 11:58.546
live with the memories of your boy.

11:58.580 --> 12:01.749
Is that the same speech you're
giving to all of the grieving?

12:05.253 --> 12:07.922
No, you're the only one I've come to see.

12:07.956 --> 12:11.092
And why is that?

12:11.126 --> 12:14.061
What makes my son so special to you?

12:14.096 --> 12:17.398
♪ ♪

12:17.432 --> 12:19.900
I don't know.

12:19.935 --> 12:22.103
♪ ♪

12:22.137 --> 12:26.507
Well... should I feel honored?

12:26.541 --> 12:28.409
When it comes to your boy,

12:28.443 --> 12:31.912
without a doubt.

12:31.947 --> 12:34.815
When it comes to me...

12:34.850 --> 12:37.918
how you feel about me,
you, sir, are entitled

12:37.953 --> 12:40.655
to feel whatever way you want.

12:40.689 --> 12:42.256
[hailer beeps]

12:42.290 --> 12:43.391
I'm sorry.

12:43.425 --> 12:44.992
It's okay. I'm tired of talking anyway.

12:45.027 --> 12:46.527
[beeping continues]

12:46.561 --> 12:48.529
Answer it. It might be important.

12:48.563 --> 12:49.697
[beeping continues]

12:49.731 --> 12:52.099
Yeah, kiddo, I'll be
there as soon as I can.

12:54.736 --> 12:57.738
Go.

12:57.773 --> 13:00.441
I appreciate you making the effort.

13:00.475 --> 13:08.482
♪ ♪

13:16.191 --> 13:18.292
(Doc) Keep your hands off my dead body.

13:18.326 --> 13:19.727
You said I could apprentice,
so let me apprentice.

13:19.761 --> 13:23.164
I was joking. Did you not pick
up on my withering sarcasm?

13:23.198 --> 13:25.499
Oh, we'll have to work
out a signal for that.

13:27.202 --> 13:28.669
[device clicks]

13:28.704 --> 13:31.939
Think you knew him? Or her?

13:31.973 --> 13:33.974
Oh, I see. The stiff's an Indogene,

13:34.009 --> 13:36.043
so of course we all know each other.

13:36.078 --> 13:39.180
Little bit of old-Earth
racism there, hey, Doc?

13:39.214 --> 13:40.648
When you were a vet, did you refuse

13:40.682 --> 13:43.184
to treat black cats as well?

13:43.218 --> 13:45.453
You done?

13:45.487 --> 13:47.388
For the moment.

13:49.624 --> 13:52.960
You seem to be pretty disturbed
by this particular corpse.

13:52.994 --> 13:55.963
You don't come across as someone
that gets disturbed very easily.

13:55.997 --> 13:59.033
What are you, a pet psychiatrist too?

13:59.067 --> 14:02.970
No, but I'm thinking of opening a practice.

14:03.004 --> 14:04.305
Hmm.

14:04.339 --> 14:06.140
[electronic beeping]

14:06.174 --> 14:07.708
There's something about
the way the skin feels.

14:07.743 --> 14:10.044
I don't like it.

14:15.183 --> 14:17.952
[beeping]

14:17.986 --> 14:20.554
Doc, that's you.

14:20.589 --> 14:22.757
[foreboding music]

14:22.791 --> 14:24.592
How can the victim be you?

14:24.626 --> 14:27.728
[beeping]

14:27.763 --> 14:30.064
♪ ♪

14:30.098 --> 14:31.966
I have no idea.

14:40.144 --> 14:42.813
[door rattles and creaks]

14:44.215 --> 14:45.449
Ready to go hunting?

14:45.483 --> 14:47.517
There was an animal attack last night.

14:47.552 --> 14:49.853
You identify the animal?

14:49.887 --> 14:52.289
Not yet.

14:52.323 --> 14:53.990
What about the victim?

14:54.025 --> 14:56.359
Doc and Samir are working on it.

15:00.431 --> 15:03.733
[exotic instrumental music playing]

15:03.768 --> 15:06.736
Given what I know about your people,

15:06.771 --> 15:10.407
what you have neglected to
tell anyone else on this planet,

15:10.441 --> 15:12.843
how do you know I won't betray you?

15:12.877 --> 15:15.245
You always do what is
in your best interest,

15:15.279 --> 15:18.048
and betraying me would not serve you well.

15:18.082 --> 15:20.684
There is that.

15:20.718 --> 15:24.888
I suppose it is your daughter,
really, who should concern you.

15:24.922 --> 15:27.224
And why is that?

15:27.258 --> 15:29.793
I believe she will betray you.

15:29.827 --> 15:32.896
Kindzi is under control.

15:32.930 --> 15:35.332
Where has she been these
last few days? Do you know?

15:35.366 --> 15:37.667
I trust her.

15:37.702 --> 15:39.903
What will she do when you wake your people?

15:39.937 --> 15:41.705
What will she tell them?

15:41.739 --> 15:44.608
My family will follow me towards peace.

15:44.642 --> 15:47.477
But your daughter offers a different path.

15:47.512 --> 15:49.513
Your family will be forced to choose.

15:49.547 --> 15:52.716
Kindzi will obey me.

15:52.750 --> 15:54.718
Of course.

15:54.752 --> 15:56.953
You know her best.

16:04.695 --> 16:06.696
An auspicious homecoming.

16:06.731 --> 16:09.399
Favi?

16:09.433 --> 16:10.600
Oh, you're alive!

16:10.635 --> 16:11.768
Oh, I was so worried.

16:11.802 --> 16:14.838
[gasps]

16:14.872 --> 16:16.573
I'm cleaning up this mess.

16:16.607 --> 16:18.808
Thank you, Andina.

16:18.843 --> 16:20.744
It's good to be home.

16:20.778 --> 16:23.747
[somber music]

16:23.781 --> 16:28.542
♪ ♪

16:28.584 --> 16:30.584
_

16:34.225 --> 16:37.194
[foreboding music]

16:37.228 --> 16:45.001
♪ ♪

16:45.036 --> 16:47.604
Lawkeeper.

16:47.638 --> 16:49.339
Kind of busy right now, T'evgin.

16:49.373 --> 16:53.009
I assure you my business
is as urgent as yours.

16:53.044 --> 16:54.144
Have you seen my daughter?

16:54.178 --> 16:55.679
No. Is she missing?

16:55.713 --> 16:57.013
She has an independent spirit.

16:57.048 --> 16:59.115
As a father, I find it... vexing.

16:59.150 --> 17:01.218
I can relate. Why don't you get upstairs,

17:01.252 --> 17:03.119
and see if you can find any tracks up top?

17:03.154 --> 17:05.121
- On it.
- Tracks?

17:05.156 --> 17:08.858
What manner of animal would
require that much firepower?

17:08.893 --> 17:11.761
♪ ♪

17:11.796 --> 17:14.864
[echoing growls]

17:14.898 --> 17:16.165
(Nolan) Wish I knew.

17:22.373 --> 17:25.108
You all right?

17:25.142 --> 17:28.444
The scene is grizzly.

17:28.479 --> 17:30.947
Yeah, that it is.

17:30.982 --> 17:33.149
You know, if you have any insight at all

17:33.184 --> 17:35.552
into what kind of creature
might have done all this damage,

17:35.586 --> 17:38.955
now would be a really good time to tell me.

17:38.990 --> 17:40.557
(Irisa) Nolan!

17:40.591 --> 17:42.392
[foreboding music]

17:42.426 --> 17:43.560
More blood up here.

17:43.594 --> 17:45.061
No tracks, but it looks like it kept eating

17:45.096 --> 17:46.096
as it headed east.

17:46.130 --> 17:47.464
Be right up there.

17:47.498 --> 17:51.234
♪ ♪

17:51.269 --> 17:53.603
You know, Defiance has
had more than it's...

18:00.945 --> 18:03.246
- Tarr wife came back.
- I heard.

18:03.281 --> 18:04.614
What's the world coming to?

18:04.649 --> 18:06.449
Terrorist gets to live in a big house,

18:06.484 --> 18:08.618
while we're out here eating rat meat.

18:08.653 --> 18:11.521
That's the goddamn <i>kwonyo
gyendo</i> for you, huh?

18:11.555 --> 18:12.889
Too true.

18:12.923 --> 18:15.325
[loud growl]

18:15.359 --> 18:16.326
What was that?

18:16.360 --> 18:18.128
[snarling]

18:18.162 --> 18:19.996
[growling]

18:20.031 --> 18:21.731
(Nolan) Hear that?

18:21.766 --> 18:23.833
[suspenseful music]

18:23.868 --> 18:25.502
[faint growl and screaming]

18:25.536 --> 18:27.070
Come on.

18:27.104 --> 18:29.539
[indistinct chatter]

18:29.573 --> 18:31.574
(man) Hear that?

18:31.609 --> 18:34.711
[growling]

18:34.745 --> 18:37.180
[screaming]

18:37.214 --> 18:39.849
[growling]

18:39.884 --> 18:42.185
[tearing and screaming]

18:42.219 --> 18:44.054
[grunts]

18:44.088 --> 18:52.028
♪ ♪

18:52.063 --> 18:53.897
God damn it!

18:53.931 --> 18:54.898
You can't blame yourself.

18:54.932 --> 18:56.066
[scratching]

18:56.100 --> 18:58.234
[gunfire]

19:00.438 --> 19:01.971
It's a raccoon.

19:05.042 --> 19:07.310
Yeah, I see that.

19:07.345 --> 19:10.213
Take a couple of hours,
get your head on straight.

19:10.247 --> 19:12.349
I'll chirp you if I find anything.

19:12.383 --> 19:14.050
You saying I can't do the job?

19:14.085 --> 19:15.819
Maybe we should ask him?

19:19.523 --> 19:21.591
Happy hunting.

19:21.625 --> 19:24.594
[somber music]

19:24.628 --> 19:25.929
♪ ♪

19:27.565 --> 19:30.567
[footsteps tapping]

19:31.802 --> 19:32.969
Oh.

19:38.843 --> 19:42.011
Have you seen much of Alak?

19:42.046 --> 19:45.815
I bring him food and
clean laundry twice a week.

19:45.850 --> 19:49.319
I do what I can to make him happy.

19:49.353 --> 19:52.188
How are his injuries?

19:52.223 --> 19:54.691
Healing well.

19:54.725 --> 19:56.726
I wish he was home, though.

19:56.761 --> 19:58.828
The McCawley house frightens me.

19:58.863 --> 20:03.466
- Afraid of ghosts?
- No, afraid of death.

20:03.501 --> 20:06.903
I think that's a very
reasonable fear, don't you?

20:06.937 --> 20:10.740
I suppose so.

20:10.775 --> 20:13.443
Poor Alak.

20:13.477 --> 20:16.780
So kind. So sad.

20:16.814 --> 20:18.348
Don't get me wrong. It's beautiful the way

20:18.382 --> 20:21.317
he loved Christie.

20:21.352 --> 20:23.920
But the dead are dead.

20:23.954 --> 20:27.590
We must mourn them and move on.

20:27.625 --> 20:30.293
Moving on is rarely easy.

20:30.327 --> 20:33.997
[somber music]

20:34.031 --> 20:36.800
Perhaps the next time you visit Alak,

20:36.834 --> 20:38.935
I will accompany you.

20:42.373 --> 20:44.274
Whatever you wish, Favi Stahma.

20:47.978 --> 20:50.547
What is it, Andina?

20:50.581 --> 20:52.415
Out with it.

20:55.286 --> 20:58.521
Alak kept his gun from the militia.

20:58.556 --> 21:00.190
There are two bullets left inside,

21:00.224 --> 21:01.424
both meant for you...

21:01.459 --> 21:05.094
one from Rafe, one from Christie.

21:05.129 --> 21:06.663
He keeps it by the front door.

21:06.697 --> 21:08.698
I would not recommend knocking.

21:08.732 --> 21:13.837
♪ ♪

21:13.871 --> 21:17.140
Thank you, for telling me.

21:17.174 --> 21:20.043
He's been through a lot.

21:20.077 --> 21:22.345
Yes.

21:22.379 --> 21:24.481
We all have.

21:24.515 --> 21:27.350
♪ ♪

21:27.384 --> 21:29.986
You still have me, Favi.

21:30.020 --> 21:33.890
♪ ♪

21:33.924 --> 21:38.061
That I do, Andina.

21:38.095 --> 21:40.296
That I do.

21:44.254 --> 21:45.788
(Samir) So who would clone you?

21:45.822 --> 21:49.358
Smart money's on the galaxy's
favorite puckered rectums,

21:49.392 --> 21:50.926
the Omec.

21:50.961 --> 21:52.294
Why?

21:52.329 --> 21:53.996
Well, aside from me being the perfect gift

21:54.030 --> 21:56.265
for birthdays, anniversaries,
and bar mitzvahs,

21:56.299 --> 22:00.436
the possibilities are
endless and depressing.

22:00.470 --> 22:01.837
You know what'd be weird?

22:01.872 --> 22:05.140
Is if that's you on the
table, and you're the clone.

22:05.175 --> 22:08.377
Or you're both clones. Or...

22:10.313 --> 22:12.615
- I'm gonna stop talking now.
- That might be best.

22:19.556 --> 22:23.893
[hissing]

22:23.927 --> 22:27.296
Uh, why does your clone's
lungs have glitter in them?

22:27.330 --> 22:30.132
They're spores.

22:30.166 --> 22:34.303
Bagra spores.

22:34.337 --> 22:36.705
They only grow in Old St. Louis.

22:36.740 --> 22:39.675
[tense music]

22:39.709 --> 22:41.477
The Omec are hiding something from us.

22:41.511 --> 22:42.611
Where are you going?

22:42.646 --> 22:44.647
♪ ♪

22:44.681 --> 22:46.882
I intend to shut those
sons of bitches down.

22:46.917 --> 22:48.817
By yourself?

22:48.852 --> 22:50.319
You know we should call Nolan and Amanda.

22:50.353 --> 22:52.354
Nolan and Amanda, right.

22:52.389 --> 22:54.023
The last time I asked those two to choose

22:54.057 --> 22:55.658
between the Omec and me,

22:55.692 --> 22:56.992
they tore a strip off my hide

22:57.027 --> 22:58.794
and used it for spare parts.

22:58.828 --> 23:01.030
Those two will pussyfoot
around and give the purples

23:01.064 --> 23:02.798
a chance to destroy evidence.

23:02.832 --> 23:04.900
No, I'm getting proof first.

23:04.935 --> 23:06.235
- Let me go with you.
- No.

23:06.269 --> 23:09.038
Why not? I can handle myself.

23:09.072 --> 23:11.807
If I'm not back by this time tomorrow,

23:11.841 --> 23:16.178
I'm counting on you to sound the alarm.

23:16.212 --> 23:19.048
[door rattles and thuds]

23:20.717 --> 23:23.686
[light rock music]

23:23.720 --> 23:24.687
♪ ♪

23:24.721 --> 23:29.058
[breathing heavily]

23:29.092 --> 23:37.700
♪ ♪

23:37.734 --> 23:43.372
(man) ♪ Don't you
know it's revolution? ♪

23:43.406 --> 23:45.708
♪ ♪

23:45.742 --> 23:48.944
♪ I'm right where I want to be ♪

23:48.979 --> 23:52.014
(Nolan voice-over) [echoing] Got
to practice this day and night

23:52.048 --> 23:53.882
till we can do it blindfolded.

23:53.917 --> 23:58.287
(man) ♪ I don't care for no solution ♪

23:58.321 --> 24:01.690
(Nolan voice-over) [echoing] That's
it. Come on. Pick those legs up.

24:01.725 --> 24:05.761
(man) ♪ I see what I want to see ♪

24:05.795 --> 24:08.063
(Nolan voice-over) I'm trying to get
these people ready to fight a battle.

24:08.098 --> 24:09.598
♪ ♪

24:09.633 --> 24:14.903
(man) ♪ Yes, I know it's such a shock ♪

24:14.938 --> 24:17.373
♪ It has to be ♪

24:17.407 --> 24:19.208
(Nolan voice-over)
It's our responsibility.

24:19.242 --> 24:21.710
(man) ♪ It has to be ♪

24:21.745 --> 24:23.479
(Nolan voice-over) There
is some real talent here.

24:23.513 --> 24:24.780
(man) ♪ And I can ♪

24:24.814 --> 24:26.115
[gunshot]

24:26.149 --> 24:29.885
(man) ♪ Feel that silver lining ♪

24:29.919 --> 24:31.920
(Nolan voice-over) Come
on. We have to get strong.

24:31.955 --> 24:33.555
♪ ♪

24:33.590 --> 24:37.126
(man) ♪ And know the
whole thing falls apart ♪

24:37.160 --> 24:39.762
(Nolan voice-over) We will face
the beast, and we will defeat him.

24:39.796 --> 24:40.863
(man) ♪ And I can see ♪

24:40.897 --> 24:43.399
[gunshot]

24:43.433 --> 24:45.334
(Nolan) This confederacy of the strong

24:45.368 --> 24:48.137
will hold the line with pride.

24:48.171 --> 24:51.640
We will face Rahm Tak,
and we will defeat him.

24:51.675 --> 24:53.142
Do we have an understanding?

24:53.176 --> 24:55.544
- Defiance!
- Defiance!

24:55.578 --> 24:56.578
(all) Defiance!

24:56.613 --> 24:59.381
(man) ♪ To just ♪

24:59.416 --> 25:01.417
♪ Turn to dust ♪

25:01.451 --> 25:03.886
[grunts]

25:03.920 --> 25:06.388
- [yells]
- ♪ Turns to dust ♪

25:06.423 --> 25:09.591
♪ ♪

25:09.626 --> 25:14.930
(man) ♪ Don't you
know it's revolution? ♪

25:14.964 --> 25:17.599
♪ ♪

25:17.634 --> 25:22.271
♪ I'm right where I want to be ♪

25:25.809 --> 25:27.176
How'd you get in here?

25:27.210 --> 25:30.012
The door was open.

25:30.046 --> 25:31.447
Where's your daughter?

25:31.481 --> 25:34.817
Don't know. Don't care.

25:34.851 --> 25:38.821
That doesn't sound
right. What troubles you?

25:38.855 --> 25:40.456
Too many dead people.

25:40.490 --> 25:43.292
[sniffs and grunts]

25:43.326 --> 25:46.361
You're hurting.

25:46.396 --> 25:47.930
I can take that pain away.

25:47.964 --> 25:52.000
I don't want it to go
away. You should leave.

25:52.035 --> 25:54.870
I like it here.

25:54.904 --> 25:57.339
Wouldn't you rather feel good,

25:57.373 --> 26:01.643
even if only for a moment?

26:01.678 --> 26:03.378
No.

26:03.413 --> 26:05.180
You're not the "feel good for a moment"

26:05.215 --> 26:07.349
type of guy, are you?

26:07.383 --> 26:10.119
I think you like to take it slow,

26:10.153 --> 26:12.688
savor the moment.

26:12.722 --> 26:16.792
[inhales and exhales deeply]

26:16.826 --> 26:19.862
[relaxed electronic music]

26:19.896 --> 26:28.604
♪ ♪

26:28.638 --> 26:31.840
No.

26:31.875 --> 26:34.343
- [growling]
- [growls] No.

26:34.377 --> 26:37.346
[foreboding music]

26:37.380 --> 26:43.719
♪ ♪

26:43.753 --> 26:47.890
That growl, the beast,
what do you know about that?

26:47.924 --> 26:50.425
What aren't you telling me?

26:50.460 --> 26:53.729
♪ ♪

26:53.763 --> 26:58.142
[growling]

27:02.866 --> 27:05.267
[groans]

27:09.606 --> 27:10.840
[groans]

27:10.874 --> 27:14.810
[hailer beeping]

27:14.845 --> 27:16.746
[door rattles]

27:16.780 --> 27:19.849
[beeping continues]

27:19.883 --> 27:22.952
[sighs]

27:22.986 --> 27:24.987
Shouldn't you answer that?

27:25.021 --> 27:26.422
Doesn't matter right now.

27:26.456 --> 27:27.556
What the hell's going on?

27:27.591 --> 27:29.525
[chuckles]

27:29.559 --> 27:32.695
Spoken like somebody who
knows exactly what's going on.

27:32.729 --> 27:35.498
- You're drunk.
- You ought to know.

27:35.532 --> 27:37.333
Well, at least I can drink
and hold myself together.

27:37.367 --> 27:38.434
Clearly you can't.

27:38.468 --> 27:39.735
[grunts]

27:39.770 --> 27:41.437
Now get out of my way.
I got to go see T'evgin.

27:41.471 --> 27:43.706
No. Why? Why?

27:43.740 --> 27:44.774
Why?

27:48.912 --> 27:51.046
'Cause him and Kindzi know
something about these attacks,

27:51.081 --> 27:52.515
something they're not telling us.

27:52.549 --> 27:54.550
All right, you're going to
go see T'evgin like this?

27:54.584 --> 27:56.719
Hmm? Come on. Sit down.

27:56.753 --> 27:58.554
Okay. Shh. Shh. Hey.

27:58.588 --> 28:01.924
Hey, in the morning, I will
go with you to the mines,

28:01.958 --> 28:03.559
and we'll get to the bottom of this.

28:06.363 --> 28:08.297
How many more people got to die?

28:13.270 --> 28:15.604
I need you to sleep this off.

28:15.639 --> 28:18.874
All right? For me. Please.

28:18.909 --> 28:21.877
[gentle music]

28:21.912 --> 28:24.480
♪ ♪

28:24.514 --> 28:27.483
[foreboding music]

28:27.517 --> 28:29.652
♪ ♪

28:29.686 --> 28:32.354
[hissing]

28:32.389 --> 28:35.991
[hissing and sputtering]

28:36.026 --> 28:37.259
[hissing]

28:37.294 --> 28:45.968
♪ ♪

28:46.002 --> 28:47.470
Great.

28:47.504 --> 28:49.839
What could possibly go wrong here?

28:49.873 --> 28:56.512
♪ ♪

28:56.546 --> 28:59.715
[door creaking]

28:59.749 --> 29:02.818
♪ ♪

29:02.853 --> 29:05.421
[gasps]

29:05.637 --> 29:08.499
_

29:09.426 --> 29:12.394
[ominous music]

29:12.429 --> 29:16.165
♪ ♪

29:16.199 --> 29:18.968
We created life. Doesn't that make us gods?

29:19.002 --> 29:21.971
Well, you won't be getting
a hosanna from me, purple.

29:22.005 --> 29:24.940
Funny. Your clones made jokes too...

29:24.975 --> 29:26.208
at first.

29:26.243 --> 29:28.110
If you try to run, you'll end up like them.

29:28.144 --> 29:29.678
If I don't, you'll kill me.

29:29.713 --> 29:31.180
Oh, I don't want you dead.

29:31.214 --> 29:34.583
Oh, so I'm misinterpreting
the big pile of parts

29:34.618 --> 29:36.085
that looks just like me.

29:36.119 --> 29:39.622
I don't care about you.
I care about the hunt.

29:39.656 --> 29:45.060
Oh, well, there's no
sport in hunting my clones.

29:45.095 --> 29:48.497
I mean, come on. Look at this girl.

29:48.532 --> 29:50.232
She's a lover, not a fighter.

29:50.267 --> 29:51.901
After years idle in deep space,

29:51.935 --> 29:53.869
I thought it best to start small.

29:53.904 --> 29:57.506
I've begun to move on
to more challenging prey.

29:57.541 --> 29:59.008
[liquid bubbling]

29:59.042 --> 30:01.744
You're going to help me hunt.

30:01.778 --> 30:05.381
- What is that?
- A control stem.

30:05.415 --> 30:09.451
It keeps you shape-takers docile.

30:09.486 --> 30:10.953
I won't let you.

30:10.987 --> 30:13.289
- Yes, you will.
- No, I mean it.

30:13.323 --> 30:14.356
You'll have to kill me.

30:14.391 --> 30:16.859
[chuckles] No.

30:16.893 --> 30:21.530
Your will to live is much too strong.

30:21.565 --> 30:24.199
- Show me your neck.
- No.

30:24.234 --> 30:26.068
If you don't, I'll snap it.

30:29.873 --> 30:32.841
[suspenseful music]

30:32.876 --> 30:37.746
♪ ♪

30:37.781 --> 30:39.114
[gasps]

30:39.149 --> 30:40.950
[screaming]

30:40.984 --> 30:45.754
[gasping and grunting]

30:45.789 --> 30:47.122
Very good.

30:47.157 --> 30:49.358
[shudders]

30:49.392 --> 30:53.295
Very good.

30:53.330 --> 30:55.598
Now pull the ax from your belt.

30:55.632 --> 30:56.932
[grunts]

30:56.967 --> 30:59.068
[gasping]

30:59.102 --> 31:02.805
♪ ♪

31:02.839 --> 31:04.139
What are you going to make me...

31:04.174 --> 31:06.942
Remain silent.

31:06.977 --> 31:09.278
Please your empty hand on the ledge.

31:09.312 --> 31:14.817
♪ ♪

31:14.851 --> 31:16.952
Now raise the ax.

31:16.987 --> 31:18.988
[ominous music]

31:19.022 --> 31:20.956
Above the hand.

31:20.991 --> 31:23.726
♪ ♪

31:23.760 --> 31:25.127
Higher.

31:25.161 --> 31:27.663
♪ ♪

31:27.697 --> 31:29.098
Higher.

31:29.132 --> 31:30.466
♪ ♪

31:30.500 --> 31:31.934
Higher.

31:31.968 --> 31:33.864
(T'evgin) Enough!

31:38.408 --> 31:40.228
What is happening here?

31:42.065 --> 31:44.666
Come, shape-taker!

31:48.471 --> 31:50.372
Go ahead.

31:54.144 --> 31:55.277
[ax clanging]

31:55.311 --> 31:57.112
Explain.

31:57.147 --> 32:00.649
Remember when I used your
drone to heal Nolan and Irisa?

32:00.683 --> 32:04.052
Well, your sweet daughter here
kept a copy of my source print

32:04.087 --> 32:06.755
and used it to make clones.

32:06.789 --> 32:09.558
- Dirty birdie.
- Stop talking.

32:10.743 --> 32:13.745
_

32:14.404 --> 32:17.521
_

32:17.800 --> 32:19.868
Go back to town; tell no
one of what you found here.

32:19.903 --> 32:22.104
Protect my interests at all costs.

32:22.138 --> 32:25.107
[tense music]

32:25.141 --> 32:26.975
♪ ♪

32:27.010 --> 32:28.844
What were you thinking?

32:28.878 --> 32:31.013
At least now I have your attention.

32:31.047 --> 32:33.415
- You are forbidden to feed.
- Why?

32:33.449 --> 32:35.851
Indogene were created
for that very purpose.

32:35.885 --> 32:38.086
And what about the Votans in Defiance?

32:38.121 --> 32:39.521
The ones you slaughtered?

32:39.556 --> 32:43.525
- Lower races.
- Sentient races.

32:46.296 --> 32:48.764
You know how intoxicating and disorienting

32:48.798 --> 32:50.032
the hunt can be.

32:50.066 --> 32:52.768
You never told me how
great the hunger can be

32:52.802 --> 32:55.304
once you've fed for the first time.

32:58.374 --> 33:00.576
Because I want more for you than that!

33:00.610 --> 33:02.277
More than what we truly are?

33:02.312 --> 33:04.246
Than what we are meant to be?

33:04.280 --> 33:06.415
You have turned your back on our people.

33:06.449 --> 33:09.017
I will lead them into a new age,

33:09.052 --> 33:11.153
one without a harvest,

33:11.187 --> 33:14.990
one that will not end
in our own extinction.

33:15.024 --> 33:18.493
I wonder what the others will
think of you when they awake?

33:18.528 --> 33:20.329
They will think I'm a pragmatist.

33:20.363 --> 33:22.664
And then when you order
them to lay in the filth

33:22.699 --> 33:25.667
beside the animals it is
their right to feed upon?

33:25.702 --> 33:28.670
We will not be denied our true nature.

33:28.705 --> 33:29.972
[device buzzing]

33:30.006 --> 33:33.675
Yes... you will!

33:33.710 --> 33:35.377
[dramatic music]

33:35.411 --> 33:38.380
[device whirring]

33:38.414 --> 33:40.749
♪ ♪

33:40.783 --> 33:45.354
[whimpering]

33:45.388 --> 33:48.657
And I am tired of teaching you.

33:48.691 --> 33:51.393
Good-bye, Kindzi.

33:54.063 --> 33:55.831
[funky bass music]

33:55.865 --> 33:58.533
(man) ♪ Nothing left for my baby ♪

33:58.568 --> 33:59.568
♪ ♪

33:59.602 --> 34:01.870
♪ More than I had to have ♪

34:01.904 --> 34:03.672
♪ ♪

34:03.706 --> 34:06.642
♪ But people say I should leave you ♪

34:06.676 --> 34:07.976
♪ ♪

34:08.011 --> 34:11.880
♪ I say I'm trying my best ♪

34:11.914 --> 34:12.914
♪ Ooh ♪

34:12.949 --> 34:14.248
Good day to you.

34:14.284 --> 34:16.385
[man singing indistinctly]

34:16.418 --> 34:18.719
I have entered a period of mourning

34:18.755 --> 34:20.989
and must apply <i>gwavo ledawo.</i>

34:23.926 --> 34:25.761
I require the darkest ink you have.

34:25.795 --> 34:27.996
Shop's closed.

34:28.031 --> 34:29.731
Clearly it is not.

34:29.766 --> 34:31.433
You blew up the arch.

34:31.467 --> 34:33.935
That she did.

34:33.969 --> 34:36.905
Here.

34:36.938 --> 34:39.007
Pretend you're selling to me.

34:48.016 --> 34:51.253
Thank you.

34:51.286 --> 34:52.621
For the pardon.

34:52.655 --> 34:55.389
Don't thank me. Thank your husband.

34:55.425 --> 34:59.161
Oh, you can't. He's dead.

35:00.563 --> 35:05.734
For what it is worth, I regret
the incident in your office.

35:05.768 --> 35:07.502
Not yet, you don't.

35:14.010 --> 35:16.244
[gagging]

35:16.279 --> 35:17.746
[exhales]

35:21.250 --> 35:23.352
About last night...

35:31.894 --> 35:33.128
All right.

35:42.972 --> 35:45.240
[plastic rustling]

35:45.274 --> 35:47.409
[footsteps tapping]

35:47.443 --> 35:49.444
Get to talking, T'evgin.

35:49.479 --> 35:51.713
What do you know about this beast?

35:51.748 --> 35:54.483
There will be no more killings.

35:54.517 --> 35:56.251
Seems you could've
mentioned knowing about 'em

35:56.285 --> 35:58.220
when you walked into my crime scene

35:58.254 --> 36:00.922
or when your daughter took
off running after the beast.

36:00.957 --> 36:02.691
There'll be no more killings.

36:02.725 --> 36:05.193
- I got your word on that?
- You have my word.

36:05.228 --> 36:06.895
On your daughter's life?

36:10.299 --> 36:12.200
On my daughter's life.

36:13.603 --> 36:15.871
Thank you, T'evgin.

36:15.905 --> 36:18.273
No! No, not good enough.

36:18.307 --> 36:20.876
I'm gonna seek justice
for the people who've died.

36:20.910 --> 36:24.413
The dead are dead, and
nothing can change that.

36:24.447 --> 36:27.716
I have said all that I need to say.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.351
(Amanda) Nolan! What are you doing?

36:29.385 --> 36:32.220
He knows more than he's letting on.

36:32.255 --> 36:33.688
[suspenseful music]

36:33.723 --> 36:36.158
Don't you, T'ev?

36:36.192 --> 36:38.360
I will afford you one opportunity

